# ── Google Drive sync configuration ─────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Sync uses the OAuth authorization-code flow, handled by Cloudflare Pages
# Functions in functions/api/oauth/. Three values are involved:
#
#   VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID   (this file / Pages build env) — public; baked into
#                           the frontend bundle. Only used to detect that sync
#                           is configured and show the sync UI.
#   GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID        (Pages Function env) — same value as above.
#   GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET    (Pages Function env) — SECRET; never ships to the
#                           browser. Lives only in Cloudflare / .dev.vars.
#
# Setup:
# 1. Create an OAuth 2.0 "Web application" client at
#    https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# 2. Add Authorized redirect URIs:
#      https://<your-pages-domain>/api/oauth/callback
#      http://localhost:8788/api/oauth/callback        (local dev)
# 3. Publish the OAuth consent screen ("In production"). While it is in
#    "Testing" status, Google expires refresh tokens after 7 days and users
#    would be forced to sign in weekly.
# 4. In the Cloudflare Pages project settings, set VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID and
#    GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID as plain text and GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET as a secret.
# 5. Locally: copy this file to .env.local, and .dev.vars.example to .dev.vars,
#    then run `npm run dev:cf` (wrangler serves the app AND the /api/oauth
#    functions on http://localhost:8788). Plain `npm run dev` still works but
#    sign-in will 404 because Vite alone doesn't serve the functions.
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
